                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A manuscript scroll with text in both kanbun and katakana-majiri
                            including coloured diagrams of the human body with acupuncture points
                            and some internal organs named, copied in the <date>first half of 19th
                                century</date>. According to the notes in English accompanying this
                            item, it was executed by <persName>Yoshida, Ikiu</persName> in
                                <date>1688</date> and was formerly property of the Yoshida family
                                <date>(1500-1910)</date>, but there is no evidence to support any of
                            these claims. </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="lzh" source="IANA">Literary Chinese</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_100">

                            <textLang otherLangs="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

